  <a href="#1" id="1">
   Berlin -- Erich Honecker, the former GDR head of state, died at his house in Santiago, Chile on Sunday morning [29 May], according to his lawyer.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Lawyer Nicolas Becker, who had represented 81-year-old Honecker before the Berlin court in 1992 and early 1993, told DPA on Sunday afternoon that Honecker had rejected an operation.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   Becker could not comment on the exact cause of Honecker's death.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   Becker said he did not know whether Honecker has left a will or where the funeral would be held.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   He also said he cannot say whether Margot Honecker, who had informed Becker of her husband's death, will be allowed to stay in Chile.
  </a>
